BAFANA Bafana and Leeds United legend Lucas Radebe has joined a number of prominent voices to urge the public to practice all safety measures to stop the spread of the deadly virus. Radebe, like many other current and former footballers, athletes, TV personalities etc, has taken to social media to spread the message regarding the importance of following measures by authorities in a fight against the deadly virus. Radebe urged people, especially those in townships, to wash their hands regularly, sanitise if possible and avoid getting too close to other people. He also took some time to thank the people who are in the front line, risking their lives to save others. "As we sat at home trying to curb the virus, Doctors,nurses,police and army (government employees)out on duty we thank you and our thoughts are with you guys for your sacrifices," he said. Watch the video below:  